                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    Can I diagnose myself using these numbers?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    No. These calculators are educational tools only. They
                    cannot diagnose or rule out any condition. Always discuss
                    abnormal or worrying results with a qualified healthcare
                    professional.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    What if my BMI is high but I’m very muscular?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    BMI does not distinguish between muscle and fat, so athletes
                    and very muscular people may have a high BMI but healthy
                    body fat levels. In that case, waist measurements, body fat
                    percentage, fitness tests, and lab markers are more
                    informative than BMI alone.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
