                    Seek urgent care if you have very high blood pressure (for
                    example, ≥ 180/120 mmHg with symptoms), chest pain, severe
                    shortness of breath, confusion, or other alarming symptoms.
                    Book a routine appointment if your BMI, waist, blood
                    pressure, or resting heart rate are consistently outside
                    healthy ranges, especially with other risk factors.
                  </p>
